=== 4.2 The Math

==== Step 1: Project to Q, K, V

Given input stem:[X \in \mathbb{R}^{T\times d}], we learn three weight matrices:

[stem]
++++
W_q \in \mathbb{R}^{d\times d_k}, \quad W_k \in \mathbb{R}^{d\times d_k}, \quad W_v \in \mathbb{R}^{d\times d_v}
++++

And compute:

[stem]
++++
Q = X W_q  \in \mathbb{R}^{T\times d_k} \quad K = X W_k  \in \mathbb{R}^{T\times d_k} \quad V = X W_v  \in \mathbb{R}^{T\times d_v}
++++

In standard single-head attention, stem:[d_k = d_v = d].

==== Step 2: Compute Attention Scores

[stem]
++++
S = Q K^{\top} / \sqrt{d_k}  \in \mathbb{R}^{T\times T}
++++

`S[i,j]` measures how relevant token `j` is to token `i`.
The division by stem:[\sqrt{d_k}] prevents the dot products from growing too large.

[NOTE]
====
*Math Minute — Matrix Multiplication*

For matrices stem:[A \in \mathbb{R}^{m\times n}] and stem:[B \in \mathbb{R}^{n\times p}]:
stem:[(AB)[i,j\] = \sum_k A[i,k\] \cdot B[k,j\]].
The result has shape stem:[[m\times p\]].
Each entry is a dot product of a row of `A` and a column of `B`.
====

==== Step 3: Apply Causal Mask (for autoregressive models)

GPT is *autoregressive*: when predicting token `t`, it must not look at tokens `t+1, t+2, …`.
We enforce this by masking the upper triangle:

[stem]
++++
M[i,j] = \begin{cases} 0 & \text{if } j \leq i \\ -\infty & \text{if } j > i \end{cases}
++++

[stem]
++++
S_{\text{masked}} = S + M
++++

Adding stem:[-\infty] before softmax effectively zeroes out those attention weights.

==== Step 4: Softmax → Attention Weights

[stem]
++++
A = \operatorname{softmax}(S_{\text{masked}}) \in \mathbb{R}^{T\times T}
++++

`A[i,j]` is now a probability: how much token `i` attends to token `j`.

==== Step 5: Weighted Sum of Values

[stem]
++++
\text{Output} = A V   \in \mathbb{R}^{T\times d_v}
++++

`Output[i]` is a weighted blend of all value vectors, guided by how much token `i` attends to each position.

*Full formula:*

[stem]
++++
\operatorname{Attention}(Q, K, V) = \operatorname{softmax}\!\left( \frac{QK^{\top}}{\sqrt{d_k}} + M \right) \cdot V
++++
